WEBVTT

00:05.380 --> 00:08.509
<i>[Aaron Embry's "Raven's Song"]</i>

00:08.509 --> 00:11.512
<i>[peaceful piano ballad]</i>

00:11.512 --> 00:17.601
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:17.601 --> 00:22.481
EMBRY: ♪ Oh, the raven's song
is short ♪

00:22.481 --> 00:24.358
♪ But it's strong ♪

00:24.358 --> 00:26.568
[music distorts]
♪ Like the mind ♪

00:26.568 --> 00:27.986
<i>MARKER: You don't really</i>
<i>want to be known</i>

00:27.986 --> 00:30.906
<i>as the guy who draws</i>
<i>boring breakfast food.</i>

00:30.906 --> 00:33.450
You can't go out like that,
because I won't let you!

00:33.450 --> 00:36.870
‐ We have got to tear
the entire system to shreds!

00:36.870 --> 00:38.413
MARKER:
Broke rhymes with woke.

00:38.413 --> 00:39.456
‐ [inhales sharply]

00:40.832 --> 00:42.626
‐ Psst.
Hey, hey. Psst.

00:42.626 --> 00:44.503
Hey. Hey, hey.
That's right.

00:44.503 --> 00:46.630
That shit really happened.

00:46.630 --> 00:47.881
‐ Oh, shit.

00:47.881 --> 00:49.883
MARKER: Haven't you heard,
Black man?

00:49.883 --> 00:52.094
The revolution is nigh.

00:52.094 --> 00:53.762
‐ Can you give me a second?
MARKER: Fine, you got one.

00:53.762 --> 00:55.055
‐ I'm not dreaming.

00:55.055 --> 00:57.641
I thought I was dreaming,
but I'm not dreaming.

00:57.641 --> 01:00.060
This is not going on
right now.

01:00.060 --> 01:02.604
[persistent ringing]
You know what to do.

01:04.648 --> 01:05.816
I'm not doing this.

01:05.816 --> 01:09.027
So you, unfortunately,
have to go.

01:09.027 --> 01:10.904
‐ I'm not going anywhere,
brother.

01:10.904 --> 01:12.239
I like fucking with you.

01:12.239 --> 01:14.324
‐ Well, you can like it
on your way out the door

01:14.324 --> 01:16.910
because last time I saw you,
you fucked my life up,

01:16.910 --> 01:19.162
and because of you,
I have to get it back.

01:19.162 --> 01:21.999
I am putting the genie
back in the bottle

01:21.999 --> 01:25.419
and the marker in the trash.

01:25.419 --> 01:27.087
MARKER:
This is not the last of me.

01:27.087 --> 01:28.463
You hear me, Keef Knight?

01:28.463 --> 01:30.507
I will not be ignored!

01:30.507 --> 01:31.883
KEEF: [grunts]
MARKER: Motherfucker!

01:31.883 --> 01:34.094
[grunting]

01:34.094 --> 01:35.804
[groans]

01:35.804 --> 01:36.847
Ow!

01:36.847 --> 01:40.475
<i>[mellow music]</i>

01:40.475 --> 01:43.061
GUNTHER: [sighs]
Damn, man,
I hope he likes this.

01:43.061 --> 01:45.647
I bought star fruit.

01:45.647 --> 01:47.774
[sighs]
Should I have made toast?

01:47.774 --> 01:48.984
I mean, I don't know.

01:48.984 --> 01:50.736
Would that be,
like, triggering?

01:50.736 --> 01:52.779
‐ Man, the last thing he needs
is to be coddled.

01:52.779 --> 01:55.240
GUNTHER: Okay, I don't see why
you have to be so harsh.

01:55.240 --> 01:56.533
He just got beat down
by the cops

01:56.533 --> 01:58.160
and shitcanned from his job.

01:58.160 --> 02:00.245
‐ Yeah, yeah.
That's like, what, a Tuesday
for black people?

02:00.245 --> 02:01.621
‐ Okay.
Hey.

02:01.621 --> 02:03.332
Keef.

02:03.332 --> 02:05.751
‐ What up, bro?
GUNTHER: H‐how you doin',
bud, hmm?

02:05.751 --> 02:08.086
Uh, we made you breakfast.

02:08.086 --> 02:09.504
‐ Why?

02:09.504 --> 02:13.467
‐ Why?
Well, uh, because...

02:13.467 --> 02:16.428
because we love you.

02:22.017 --> 02:23.352
Okay.
I'll take that.

02:23.352 --> 02:25.729
[laughs]
Thumbs up‐‐you see that?

02:25.729 --> 02:26.897
[phone chimes]

02:26.897 --> 02:29.107
It's a step
in the right direction.

02:29.107 --> 02:32.152
Oh, what‐‐is that Trina?
She actually texted me.

02:32.152 --> 02:34.446
‐ Talk to your woman, dawg.
She worried about you.

02:34.446 --> 02:35.864
‐ Yeah.
I'm going to, okay?

02:35.864 --> 02:37.407
I'm just gonna hit her back

02:37.407 --> 02:39.451
as soon as I get all this stuff
straightened out, you know?

02:39.451 --> 02:41.578
GUNTHER: Yeah, yeah.
‐ Straightened out?

02:41.578 --> 02:43.914
What plan you got
to un‐shit this bed?

02:43.914 --> 02:44.998
‐ That's very funny.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.667
I'll have you know
I'm on my way

02:46.667 --> 02:48.460
to Bloom & Hill as we speak.

02:48.460 --> 02:50.796
I am not gonna let my life
get destroyed

02:50.796 --> 02:52.881
over one unfortunate episode.

02:52.881 --> 02:54.341
‐ [laughs]
Episode?

02:54.341 --> 02:56.885
Oh, you‐‐you think
that was an episode?

02:56.885 --> 02:58.845
Shit, that was more like
the series finale.

02:58.845 --> 03:01.139
You went full‐blown crazy.
You lost your damn mind.

03:01.139 --> 03:02.974
KEEF: Guys, guys, look at me!

03:02.974 --> 03:04.893
Don't I look fine?

03:04.893 --> 03:06.353
[forced laugh]

03:06.353 --> 03:08.689
Don't I look stress‐free
and carefree?

03:08.689 --> 03:10.816
I got my eight hours of sleep,
all right?

03:10.816 --> 03:12.234
It is a new day.

03:12.234 --> 03:14.403
It is a new attitude.

03:14.403 --> 03:15.737
‐ Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

03:15.737 --> 03:17.447
When you go in there,
don't apologize.

03:17.447 --> 03:20.075
Pretend that shit
didn't happen, all right?

03:20.075 --> 03:22.369
I'm just saying.
Look, if you pretend
it didn't happen,

03:22.369 --> 03:24.121
eventually maybe
they'll start to think,

03:24.121 --> 03:25.580
"Maybe that shit
didn't happen."

03:25.580 --> 03:27.207
‐ Like the prequels.

03:27.207 --> 03:28.792
‐ What prequels?

03:28.792 --> 03:29.918
Jar Jar who?

03:29.918 --> 03:31.378
‐ No ho ho, okay?

03:31.378 --> 03:33.088
Jar Jar happened.

03:33.088 --> 03:35.048
Meesa thinks
you need to deal with it.

03:35.048 --> 03:36.925
‐ Let me tell you something,
it's like that time

03:36.925 --> 03:38.677
when my dad
got that lady pregnant

03:38.677 --> 03:39.845
and he had that kid.

03:39.845 --> 03:42.222
He just pretended
that shit didn't happen

03:42.222 --> 03:44.141
and eventually, my mom...

03:44.141 --> 03:46.852
my mom forgot
all about that kid.

03:46.852 --> 03:49.271
[whispering]
What kid? Hmm?

03:49.271 --> 03:52.232
‐ Okay, but you definitely
still have a sister.

03:52.232 --> 03:55.360
‐ [whispers] No.
‐ So all I have to do

03:55.360 --> 03:57.988
is pretend
that Golden Con never happened.

03:57.988 --> 03:59.990
I think I can do‐‐I mean,
I'm pretty good at improv.

03:59.990 --> 04:01.199
‐ No, you're not.

04:01.199 --> 04:03.702
You need to stay home
and self‐medicate.

04:03.702 --> 04:05.662
Dude, you went toastal.

04:05.662 --> 04:08.248
You were kickboxing
a cardboard cutout.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.499
You remember.
‐ Hold on, hold on.

04:09.499 --> 04:10.500
‐ Huh?

04:10.500 --> 04:11.960
‐ What cardboard cutout?

04:11.960 --> 04:13.712
‐ Mm.
I didn't see it.

04:13.712 --> 04:16.006
‐ At the Q and A.
‐ What Q and A?

04:16.006 --> 04:17.424
‐ What is a Q and A?

04:17.424 --> 04:18.633
‐ Okay, it happened.

04:18.633 --> 04:20.719
<i>I</i> was there.

04:20.719 --> 04:22.262
‐ You were where?

04:22.262 --> 04:23.680
‐ The Q and A.

04:23.680 --> 04:24.681
‐ What Q and A?

04:24.681 --> 04:25.891
‐ The one
where you were kickboxing

04:25.891 --> 04:27.434
the cardboard cutout!
[tense laugh]

04:27.434 --> 04:28.727
‐ What cardboard cutout?

04:28.727 --> 04:30.562
‐ No, you can't just repeat
everything I say!

04:30.562 --> 04:32.314
That's not improv!
God damn it.

04:32.314 --> 04:35.317
<i>[rock music]</i>

04:35.317 --> 04:40.906
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:45.035 --> 04:48.038
<i>[upbeat guitar music]</i>

04:48.038 --> 04:51.124
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:51.124 --> 04:52.501
‐ Hey.
How you doing, my man?

04:52.501 --> 04:54.085
‐ What's up, Mr. Knight?

04:54.085 --> 04:55.754
‐ Thanks, man.
Uh, need me to sign in?

04:55.754 --> 04:57.088
‐ Nah, you're good, man.
Go ahead.

04:57.088 --> 04:59.758
‐ Cool, cool, cool.
‐ It's all good.

05:01.593 --> 05:03.762
‐ Ah.
Oh, well, if you insist.

05:03.762 --> 05:05.222
[laughs]

05:05.222 --> 05:07.390
Okay.
Thank you.

05:07.390 --> 05:09.601
Thank you.
Oh.

05:09.601 --> 05:11.686
Margaret, it is so good
to see you.

05:11.686 --> 05:14.064
You get the flowers I sent you?
They must be lost in the mail.

05:14.064 --> 05:16.691
Uh, I'm here for a meeting
with Phil and Cindy.

05:16.691 --> 05:19.027
‐ Is Cindy expecting you?

05:19.027 --> 05:21.363
‐ Yeah, I think‐‐
yes, she possibly might be.

05:21.363 --> 05:23.824
I think yes, she is, so...

05:23.824 --> 05:25.909
Mm‐hmm.
‐ Yeah.

05:28.078 --> 05:29.579
Let me just check real quick.

05:29.579 --> 05:31.081
‐ Yeah, yeah, she‐‐yeah.

05:31.081 --> 05:33.583
'Cause you can call her.
She knows who I am, so...

05:34.709 --> 05:36.336
Love the sweater, by the way.

05:36.336 --> 05:38.380
[whispering]
It's very Michelle O.

05:38.380 --> 05:40.340
The double bow?
Girl, you better stop.

05:40.340 --> 05:42.008
[laughs]

05:42.008 --> 05:44.594
‐ I have Keef Knight
in the lobby.

05:44.594 --> 05:45.804
No, he‐‐

05:45.804 --> 05:47.973
I'm serious.
He's here.

05:47.973 --> 05:49.891
In person.

05:49.891 --> 05:51.893
Okay.

05:51.893 --> 05:53.311
Okay.

05:53.311 --> 05:56.356
<i>[tense music]</i>

05:56.356 --> 06:03.071
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:06.199 --> 06:07.367
‐ Keef!
‐ Cindy.

06:07.367 --> 06:08.493
CINDY: What a surprise.

06:08.493 --> 06:09.619
‐ Hey.
Um...

06:09.619 --> 06:10.912
‐ Hi.

06:10.912 --> 06:12.622
KEEF: Come and sit‐‐
‐ No, no, no.

06:12.622 --> 06:13.623
Stay there.
Stay there.

06:13.623 --> 06:16.167
‐ I can sit there‐‐okay.

06:16.167 --> 06:17.502
CINDY: [laughs]

06:22.966 --> 06:24.509
I assumed you would start.

06:24.509 --> 06:25.677
‐ Yeah.
Oh, no.

06:25.677 --> 06:27.178
Of course I'm gonna‐‐
I'm gonna start.

06:27.178 --> 06:28.513
[both laugh]

06:28.513 --> 06:29.973
So excited, you know,

06:29.973 --> 06:33.393
to really just get the ball
rolling on syndication.

06:33.393 --> 06:36.271
You know what I mean?
Um, looking forward to it.

06:36.271 --> 06:37.898
So many deadlines, right?

06:37.898 --> 06:39.357
What to do?
That's the question.

06:39.357 --> 06:42.986
‐ So we're just gonna pretend
Golden Con never happened?

06:42.986 --> 06:44.946
‐ Golden what?

06:44.946 --> 06:46.907
‐ You're not serious, are you?

06:46.907 --> 06:48.658
‐ Serious about what?
‐ Golden Con.

06:48.658 --> 06:49.993
‐ Golden who?
‐ It happened.

06:49.993 --> 06:51.036
‐ What happened?
‐ Golden Con.

06:51.036 --> 06:52.120
‐ What about it?
‐ It happened!

06:52.120 --> 06:53.705
‐ Okay! Okay, it happened!
Jesus!

06:53.705 --> 06:55.373
I'm sorry, okay?
I don't‐‐

06:55.373 --> 06:58.043
I don't know
what came over me, all right?

06:58.043 --> 06:59.628
But let me assure you,

06:59.628 --> 07:01.671
my actions do not express,
in any way,

07:01.671 --> 07:04.758
how I feel
about you fine people.

07:04.758 --> 07:06.426
CINDY: Look, Bloom & Hill‐‐

07:06.426 --> 07:09.888
well, we're not sure
we're the right fit

07:09.888 --> 07:11.931
for this new direction
you've taken.

07:11.931 --> 07:14.768
It's‐‐it's not you, it's us.

07:14.768 --> 07:16.478
‐ Cindy, Cindy, listen to me.

07:16.478 --> 07:17.646
Please don't do this, okay?

07:17.646 --> 07:20.273
I have not taken
a new direction.

07:20.273 --> 07:22.734
My coordinates are...
[beeps]

07:22.734 --> 07:24.778
[laughs]
I mean, you get it, right?

07:24.778 --> 07:27.989
Growing up as a...

07:27.989 --> 07:30.492
Asian...woman?

07:30.492 --> 07:31.951
As an Asian or something?

07:31.951 --> 07:33.495
Growing up as an Asian
or something woman‐‐

07:33.495 --> 07:36.456
‐ I'm gonna let
that Asian comment slide.

07:38.375 --> 07:40.335
You really think
you can get up on that stage

07:40.335 --> 07:42.212
and pop off like that
and recover?

07:42.212 --> 07:43.922
‐ To be honest,
I thought maybe‐‐

07:43.922 --> 07:46.841
‐ It doesn't work that way
for people like us.

07:46.841 --> 07:48.885
You think I don't ever
wanna throw an iPad

07:48.885 --> 07:50.679
out of one of these
stuffy‐ass windows,

07:50.679 --> 07:54.474
watch the glass pour down,
pick up a piece, and...

07:54.474 --> 07:56.142
slit an executive's throat?

07:56.142 --> 07:57.894
But I follow the rules.

07:57.894 --> 08:00.647
I read the fine print.
You didn't.

08:00.647 --> 08:02.565
‐ No, no, I have.
I definitely have, I know‐‐

08:02.565 --> 08:04.693
‐ Oh, you could've been
a legend!

08:06.820 --> 08:08.655
John Legend.
‐ [softly] John Legend.

08:08.655 --> 08:10.156
CINDY: He did it the right way.

08:10.156 --> 08:11.783
First he got the money,

08:11.783 --> 08:14.119
then he got the woke.

08:14.119 --> 08:16.329
You think he could've released
"Preach" right out of the gate?

08:16.329 --> 08:17.747
No.

08:17.747 --> 08:21.835
He had to do at least ten years
of "Ordinary People"

08:21.835 --> 08:23.837
before he could take that risk.

08:23.837 --> 08:27.048
That's what we have to be
to come up in this world.

08:27.048 --> 08:29.217
Ordinary.

08:31.052 --> 08:33.096
‐ [scoffs]
I get it.

08:33.096 --> 08:36.099
And I'm so glad you said that,
because now...

08:36.099 --> 08:38.810
now it's confirmed that
we're on the exact same page.

08:38.810 --> 08:41.604
Look!
I'm <i>Toast‐N‐Butter</i> man!

08:41.604 --> 08:43.898
Gentle laughs,
sweet observations.

08:43.898 --> 08:46.484
I'm the exact same guy.
Nothing has changed.

08:47.360 --> 08:50.113
‐ Well, according to
<i>The Bay Arean...</i>

08:52.115 --> 08:53.533
Everything's changed.

08:53.533 --> 08:55.076
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:55.076 --> 08:57.662
‐ Fuck Toast!
Fuck Butter!

08:57.662 --> 08:58.663
Yeah!

08:58.663 --> 09:00.749
Oh.
Okay.

09:00.749 --> 09:04.002
CINDY:
That was like the world's
worst TED Talk.

09:04.002 --> 09:05.378
‐ [softly]
Yeah, definitely, um...

09:05.378 --> 09:07.839
[indistinct shouting]

09:07.839 --> 09:09.299
I can‐‐I can fix that.

09:09.299 --> 09:11.718
[screaming]

09:11.718 --> 09:14.721
<i>[upbeat jazzy music]</i>

09:14.721 --> 09:16.681
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:16.681 --> 09:19.684
[people chatting]

09:25.482 --> 09:27.776
[quietly] Ayana.

09:27.776 --> 09:31.112
‐ Oh, shit!
Keef X in the flesh!

09:31.112 --> 09:33.531
Yes!
[applause]

09:33.531 --> 09:35.283
Yes.

09:35.283 --> 09:36.993
[applause dies down]

09:36.993 --> 09:38.661
‐ You have to take
that video down.

09:38.661 --> 09:40.872
‐ Uh...no.

09:40.872 --> 09:41.998
‐ No?

09:41.998 --> 09:43.416
‐ No.

09:44.542 --> 09:47.170
You told off a piece of toast
in blackface.

09:47.170 --> 09:48.421
That shit stays up.

09:48.421 --> 09:50.715
‐ Okay, look,
I was not in my right mind.

09:50.715 --> 09:53.051
I was distressed.
Things happened.

09:53.051 --> 09:54.803
‐ What things?
KEEF: I don't know, things.

09:54.803 --> 09:56.262
Doesn't matter.

09:56.262 --> 09:58.515
What matters is that I had
a momentary lapse in reason.

09:58.515 --> 10:01.184
‐ You sounded reasonable to me.
‐ Yes, because
I sounded like you.

10:01.184 --> 10:03.019
‐ Hmm, yeah.

10:03.019 --> 10:05.230
But you had
a "come to Black Jesus" moment.

10:05.230 --> 10:06.606
Now you wanna walk it back?

10:06.606 --> 10:08.358
I was proud of you.

10:08.358 --> 10:09.901
[phone chimes]

10:11.903 --> 10:13.154
[phone clicks]

10:13.154 --> 10:14.823
‐ Look,

10:14.823 --> 10:16.783
I'm not sure
who you think I am,

10:16.783 --> 10:18.451
but I'm not that guy.

10:18.451 --> 10:21.121
I'm just a guy who wants
to get his life back, okay?

10:21.121 --> 10:23.873
‐ I hate to say it,
but once your eyes are open,

10:23.873 --> 10:25.542
you can't unsee.

10:25.542 --> 10:27.293
‐ Yeah, but it doesn't mean
I can't try.

10:27.293 --> 10:29.170
And the longer
that video stays up,

10:29.170 --> 10:30.588
the harder it gets.

10:30.588 --> 10:33.633
‐ You think you can scrub
the Internet clean?

10:33.633 --> 10:35.343
[chuckles]

10:35.343 --> 10:36.636
KEEF:
Wait, what?
What are you doing?

10:36.636 --> 10:39.139
AYANA:
[laughs]
You're a meme now.

10:39.139 --> 10:41.099
KEEF:
Oh, my God.
I'm a meme.

10:41.099 --> 10:43.685
Fuck‐‐fuck‐‐fuck‐‐
fuck Toast‐N‐Butter!

10:43.685 --> 10:46.146
[in slow motion]
Fuck you.

10:46.146 --> 10:49.190
I am‐‐I am‐‐I am the sausage!

10:49.190 --> 10:51.901
[sobs]

10:51.901 --> 10:53.987
Oh, my God.
Just shoot me in the face.

10:53.987 --> 10:55.697
[gunshot, woman screams]
Jamal!

10:55.697 --> 10:56.948
Fuck Toast‐N‐Butter!

10:56.948 --> 10:58.241
Fuck
Toast‐N‐Butter!

10:58.241 --> 11:00.160
[hitch‐pitched]
Fuck Toast‐N‐Butter!

11:00.160 --> 11:01.661
Aw, shit.

11:01.661 --> 11:04.289
‐ I like it.
You have stage presence.

11:04.289 --> 11:05.957
‐ I feel like you enjoy
watching me suffer.

11:05.957 --> 11:07.959
‐ I barely know you.

11:07.959 --> 11:09.002
But yes.
KEEF: Okay.

11:09.002 --> 11:10.837
Okay.
[sighs]

11:10.837 --> 11:12.589
If you were me,
what would you do?

11:12.589 --> 11:14.549
‐ Honestly?
‐ Honestly, if you were me.

11:15.550 --> 11:16.759
‐ Buckle up.

11:16.759 --> 11:20.597
<i>[bass riff]</i>

11:20.597 --> 11:22.015
<i>[seatbelt clicks]</i>

11:27.228 --> 11:31.107
<i>[Cover of Carpenters'</i>
<i>"Rainy Days And Mondays"]</i>

11:31.107 --> 11:32.692
SINGER:
♪ Talking to myself ♪

11:32.692 --> 11:34.235
[phone chimes]

11:34.235 --> 11:38.865
SINGER: ♪ And feeling old ♪

11:38.865 --> 11:42.785
♪ Sometimes I'd like to quit ♪

11:42.785 --> 11:46.789
♪ Nothin' ever seems to fit ♪

11:46.789 --> 11:51.419
♪ Rainy days and Mondays
always get me down ♪

11:51.419 --> 11:53.213
‐ Sir?

11:53.213 --> 11:54.464
Sir.

11:54.464 --> 11:57.258
<i>SINGERS:</i>
<i>♪ Rainy days and Mondays ♪</i>

11:57.258 --> 11:59.135
‐ Do you mind turning that off?

11:59.135 --> 12:02.555
I've had a very shitty day.

12:02.555 --> 12:05.058
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:05.058 --> 12:06.476
[music turns off]

12:10.230 --> 12:15.193
